==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|GenAm}} {{IPA|/əˈbeɪt.ə/|/əˈbeɪt.ɚ/}}

===Etymology 1===
{{suffix|abate|or|t1=to enter without right after the owner dies and before the heir takes over}}.<ref name=WID>{{R:MW3 1976}}</ref> From {{etyl|xno|en}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}
 
# {{context|legal|lang=en}} A person who, without right, enters into a [[freehold]] on the death of the last [[possessor]], before the heir or [[devisee]]. {{defdate|Mid 16<sup>th</sup> century.}} <ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=2}}</ref>

===Etymology 2===
{{suffix|abate|or|t1=do away with}}.<ref name=WID/> From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|legal|lang=en}} One who abates, ends, or does away with a [[nuisance]]. {{defdate|Late 16<sup>th</sup> century.}} <ref name=SOED/>

